%% Diagram: Encrypted ClientHello — outer cover SNI vs inner real SNI
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant Resolver as DoH/DoT Resolver
    participant CDN as Server (shared frontend)
    participant App as Origin (example.com)

    C->>Resolver: HTTPS / SVCB query for example.com (over DoH/DoT)
    Resolver-->>C: HTTPS RR + ECHConfigList (target HPKE pubkey)
    Note over C: Tampered DNS strips ECHConfig →\nencrypted-DNS dependency is mandatory
    C->>CDN: TLS ClientHelloOuter\nSNI = public_name (e.g. cloudflare-ech.com)\necho_outer_extensions = [...]
    Note right of C: ClientHelloInner is HPKE-encrypted with ECHConfig:\nSNI = example.com, ALPN, etc.
    CDN->>CDN: HPKE-decrypt ClientHelloInner using private key
    CDN->>App: Route request to inner SNI = example.com
    CDN-->>C: ServerHello + cert for example.com
    Note over C,CDN: On-path observer sees TLS to public_name only.\nIf decryption fails → ECH retry_configs in extension.
